OL,3,C'Truly squalid': Prison reform charity
OL,4,Creacts to Winchester Prison report
OL,6,FCharlie Taylor, HM Deputy Chief
OL,7,FInspector of Prisons said: "There was
OL,8,Fno denying the failings in leadership
OL,9,Fat this prison. A full complement of
OL,10,Fprison officers had been recruited and
OL,11,Fstaff-prisoner relationships were
OL,12,Fbenign, but too many staff lacked
OL,13,Fcompetence and confidence. We found
OL,14,Fsome motivated middle managers, but
OL,15,Fmost lacked experience.
OL,17,F"Not enough had been done by leaders
OL,18,Fto make sure processes worked
OL,19,Fconsistently, that standards were
OL,20,Fenforced or that prisoners' basic
OL,21,Fneeds were met.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/10
